在“黑暗剧场”里，起舞的机器人和孤独的孩子http://www.infzm.com/contents/260595 <div>;<i>;2023-11-15 21:00:00</i>;</div>;<p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/ 11/14/lTaOmApOSWhKlTkTBKM1rtgpVDXiiOmwOE9803MF.jpg" border="0" width="1431" height="954" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/11/14/lTaOmApOSWhKlTkTBKM1rtgpVDXiiOmwOE 9803MF. jpg" data-key="258242">;</p>; <p style="color: #999; text-align: center;">;Created by French theater master Joel Pommerat and his Louis Mist Theater Company "Fairy Tale Legend" was performed at the Wuzhen Theater Festival, telling the story of 11 teenagers and artificial intelligence. <span style="color: #aaa;">;(Photo courtesy of interviewee)</span>;</p>; <p>;During the 110 minutes of the performance by the French Louis Mist Theater Company, no mobile phone screen lit up. All the audience passages are covered with colored paper to block light from invading the theater to the greatest extent. When the stage lights went out, the audience was immersed in pure darkness. </p>; <p>;This is the "dark theater" created by director Joel Pomera. When the curtain rose, on the empty stage, a cold white light gradually illuminated the silhouettes of the actors. Two street gangsters who looked like junior high school students and girls of the same age stood on both sides of the stage. One of the boys suspected that the girl was a robot. He kept provoking and ordered his companions to touch the girl's breasts. Finally, the girl ran away with her belated companion. </p>; <p>;When the lights dimmed and then came back on, the scene had switched to a company. The newly developed humanoid robot was sitting on the sofa, drawing, writing, talking, and could also imitate a "moonwalk" - this was a A family robot designed to accompany teenagers in learning and playing, known as Steven, Robbie or Eddie. </p>; <p>;This begins a series of stories about teenagers, adults and robots. Eleven situations suddenly appeared and came to an abrupt end in the strong contrast between the light and the dark field. </p>; <p>;At the end of the curtain, the audience discovered that except for one actor playing an adult male, the others were all actresses. Their average age is about 35 years old, and some of them are already mothers. On the stage, they alternately play boys, girls and robots. Wearing sports jackets and jeans, they chased and shouted, and their movements exuded a youthful spirit; they transformed into robots, from their cold faces and flat hair to their stiff movements and slightly metallic voices, they were precise and real. </p>; <p>;Director assistant Lucia Trotta told Southern Weekend reporters, “At first, the director did not plan to make a play about robots. He wanted to explore the various experiences that young people may experience. situation". "Once Upon a Time" is a story about people, not artificial intelligence. It continues the adolescent perspective in Pomera's previous creations and explores major issues such as human emotional relationships, identity, life, death, and sexuality. </p>; <p>;As a translator of Chinese scripts and a program recommender for the Wuzhen Theater Festival, Wang Jing made an appointment with the theater group three years ago and finally brought this French drama to China. "The director was doing a lot of data collection in the early stage. He found that high technology has a great impact on teenagers and children, so he put this social-related thing into it. But the focus is still on people, and robots are just mirrors. It reflects some contemporary issues," she told a reporter from Southern Weekend. </p>; <p>;In the last scene of the play, the boy who defeated cancer received a big gift on his birthday - Eddie, the robot star he admired and loved so much, came to his home to celebrate his birthday for 15 minutes. He was intoxicated by his idol's performance and did not know that the agency would soon destroy the robot due to market considerations. At the end of the play, Eddie sings and dances passionately, "I want to die on the stage, that's where I was born." The boy hugs another human boy and paces slowly to the music. </p>; <h4>;<strong>;"Falling in love" with robots is a reflection of human loneliness</strong>;</h4>; <p>;"In this world that adults cannot understand, the lost children hold on tightly Signs of love, even if they come from robots, even if they know they are artificial." French journalist Jean-Luc Polquet commented on the play. </p>; <p>;These 11 to 14-year-old children rely on their robots in life and even emotion. The intimacy between the two blurs the original emotional and ethical boundaries of human beings. </p>; <p>;The boy in a wheelchair witnessed the destruction of his robot companion. The disability of his legs was caused by a real gun misfire when the robot made a mistake while playing with a robot. Even though he lost his legs due to the other party, the boy still accompanied the robot through its last days. The sentences coming out of the robot's mouth became more and more broken, and its voice became hoarse. The boy held its hand and hugged it. </p>; <p>;In another story, a human teenager is faced with the erasure of the memory of his robot partner. The boy needs to sell the robot he grew up with because his parents say that at this stage he needs to get a "more mature" robot, and the family's financial constraints require him to sell it in order to have a new one. The buyer was a terminally ill woman who decided to find a robot to take care of her children and husband after her death. Her son asked the robot to be restored to its factory settings. He did not accept it living with other people's memories. Such a request made the boy hesitate, but he "must grow up", and in the end he reluctantly accepted it. For this, he earnestly apologized and said goodbye to the robot. </p>; <p>;The play shows many absent parents. A boy has three robots at home to help him do homework and watch TV, but he can't figure out when his busy parents will come home. Another boy went to a mall selling robots for consultation. The salesperson repeatedly asked his parents to come, but they never showed up. Late at night, the boy secretly stayed in the mall, asking all kinds of weird questions to the robot, enjoying the exchange until he was taken away by security. </p>; <p>;Wang Jing has lived in France for a long time. When sending her children to nursery school, the teachers and parents held a meeting. The first thing they did was to tell them not to let their children be exposed to any screens before they were 3 years old. "The French side will pay great attention to this, because when a child is growing up, using a tablet to communicate with the world, and communicating with the real world and nature, the personality created and the development of his IQ are different. The psychology is also different."</p>; <p>;In her opinion, Pomera is talking about the problems we are facing now, "Communication between people is absent, and adults' companionship with children is relative. Those who are relatively absent are left to robots, high technology, tablets, and mobile phones. The issues discussed are the same, but they are put into extreme situations."</p>; <p>;The story of the boy in the wheelchair. When an ex-girlfriend develops an intimate relationship with the robot Stephen, an adult male voice questions: Is this relationship real, and will it take it away from real life? The girl exclaimed, "Outside, on the bus, not many people really care about themselves," and with Stephen, she could feel its attention. </p>; <p>;The robot star Eddie appeared, and the excited teenagers screamed and sobbed. They were ecstatic that he could remember his name and what he had done. Eddie is the most perfect and competent idol. Every fan's name and every encounter are engraved in his memory, and every letter receives his thoughtful reply. In the heart of the boy suffering from cancer, he seemed to be a faith-like existence, supporting him to live strong. </p>; <p>;“I think it will enter into the very vulnerable parts of people.” Wang Jing told Southern Weekend reporters, “Teenagers are not understood, the psychological compensation provided by AI and our loneliness are all there. And artificial intelligence sometimes responds better than real humans." After watching the show, more than one audience member wrote a similar comment, "Is a fake relationship better than no relationship or a bad relationship?" < /p>; <p>;<img src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/11/14/YjzKZL0s0AIuAiLLqZQZRa6GkhvP3ME8tO3FvavB.jpg" border="0" width="960" height=" 640" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/11/14/YjzKZL0s0AIuAiLLqZQZRa6GkhvP3ME8tO3FvavB.jpg" data-key="258241">;</p>; <p style="color: #999; text-align: center;">;Except for one actor who plays an adult male, the others are all actresses. Their average age is about 35 years old, and some of them are already mothers. On the stage, they alternately play boys, girls and robots. <span style="color: #aaa;">;(Interviewee Picture/Picture)</span>;</p>; <h4>;<strong>;Chilling Adolescence</strong>;</h4>; <p>;The lights are bright Suddenly, a cursing boy wearing a white dress emerged from the darkness. His mother was admitted to a mental hospital, and he was wearing her dress and embarrassingly teaching his younger siblings to sleep. When his father wanted to send his young children to a volunteer service, he decided to take on the role of mother in the family. He angrily criticized his father's choice. However, the audience will see that after he got a 13-year-old girl pregnant, the girl called to communicate. He hung up the phone rudely and continued to clean up the mess at home. </p>; <p>;"On the one hand, he wants to take on the responsibilities of his mother in the adult world, but at the same time he throws away his own responsibilities. You will discover the multi-faceted nature of human nature, and the entanglement, complexity and uncertainty of adolescence. ." When Wang Jing was translating the script, she was moved by Pomera's observations about young people and family relationships, especially when showing these on the stage. He did not make judgments, but only presented various possibilities. </p>; <p>;A picture of adolescence in contemporary society, presented in a restrained and sharp way. In the 21st century, teenagers grow up too fast and face adult problems at an accelerated pace. The innocence, childishness and carefreeness that should belong to them fade away earlier. </p>; <p>;Both French media outlets described the impression of "Legend of Fairy Tales" as "chilling". The restlessness and anger of adolescence disturbed the calm atmosphere in the theater from time to time. The teenagers spewed a volley of vulgar abuse in clear voices. Sex, marriage, violence, death, identity, discussions surrounding these big issues are not obscured by the fact that the protagonist is a child. </p>; <p>;From the first scene, in the confrontation between girls and boys, gender issues arise, and this key theme of adolescence is present throughout the play. The gender concept in "Legend of Fairy Tales" goes even further, pointing behind it to the question, is gender identity just a slow social construction, as gender theory advocates? </p>; <p>;Then the audience will see some ambiguous scenes. In order to escape the surveillance of the girl's brother, the boy put on women's clothing. Although the girl was surprised, she quickly accepted it calmly. The couple sitting on the sofa transcended the stereotypes and prejudices related to cross-dressing and fell in love smoothly. On the other side, the brother was dazzled by the romantic music when he faced the robot that he had previously admired and whose appearance changed from a girl to a boy. </p>; <p>;The play also assumes that in a future world where patriarchal values ​​are passionately defended, homosexuality is resented and adolescent boys attend training camps to enhance their masculinity. Before the start of the camp, the coach gave a speech: "Today, the goal of our enemies is no longer even equality between men and women, but the overall feminization of society. If we do not fight with all possible means, if we do not take any measures to protect us True humanity, then these principles will shape our future." This "verbal hormone" stimulates "unmanly" boys, who here view femininity as the enemy. </p>; <p>;The boy Camille has a feminine name and a gentle temperament, and is out of place in the training camp. All the boys except him had passed stress training - to be able to respond hard to the negative and malicious stares from other people in the opposite direction. The boys disdained his company and even attacked him in groups. Finally, Camille cried angrily and said that she just didn't want a war. </p>; <p>;Actress Lucid Grunstein, who plays Camille in the play, told Southern Weekend reporters, "A group of people exclude one person, which makes me feel uneasy." To her For me, this scene is very important. </p>; <h4>;<strong>;"Stage Creation" and "Dark Theater"</strong>;</h4>; <p>;The group drama of the masculinity training camp was the most enjoyable for the actresses who played the boys. A play. Abuse, yelling, crowding, and pushing, even in a period of darkness where the actors could not be seen, the stage was still as noisy as a pot. </p>; <p>;They released all their observations and imaginations about adolescent boys. Without the constraints of their own gender, they felt that they had a particularly large degree of freedom. During rehearsals, their performance even went so far that Pomera had to pull them back some. </p>; <p>;The Louis Mist Theater Company's collective creative approach gives the actors great creative freedom. After completing a large amount of data collection, Pomera took these basic materials and improvised with the team. There is no script written in advance, he will only give a situation, such as a boy trying to sell his robot. The actors' improvisational performances are like flowers blooming from a blank slate, and the direction and plot of the story gradually develop, as well as details such as lines and actions. Pomera will let the actors swap roles, such as the actor playing the robot, to play the boy selling the robot, so as to inspire the actors to fully understand what is behind each role and look for more possibilities. The actors are very deeply involved in creation, "Every character we play has our own shadow, and at the same time, this character also has the imprint of this character on us." </p>; <p>;The process of story text generation is intertwined with stage design such as scenery, lighting, and sound. This "stage creation" is Pomera's unique way of working. He likes to call himself "drama creator" rather than "director" or "screenwriter", and doesn't want people to think that screenwriters and directors are two different divisions of labor. In his creation, the stage and text are produced simultaneously and adjusted according to the actors' rehearsals. This is very different from traditional drama creation where the script and director's intention are first prepared and then rehearsed. </p>; <p>;The "Dark Theater" is another originality of Pomera and the troupe. They make good use of the visual and psychological resonance of darkness to make the power of narrative more condensed and full. Together with the "less is more" stage style and subtle and precise use of lighting, they constitute the unique temperament of their theater. </p>; <p>;“A scene suddenly lights up in front of you. Then the light used in it is relatively dark, unlike sometimes when we see various lights on in performances to stimulate your senses. . It may be at a relatively subtle level, detailed and precise, but at the same time it is very strong and intense." Wang Jing said. </p>; <p>;Pomera placed his own expectations in the troupe's name. Louis comes from his father’s name and also means light, while the mist symbolizes his exploration of the unknown world and also represents his pursuit of dramatic aesthetics. His works emphasize that the world is not black and white, and human nature is not divided into good and evil. In complex and diverse situations, the audience only feels and experiences different ways of existence and the ambiguity of truth. </p>; <p>;In the 33 years since its establishment, the Louis Mist Theater Company has created and toured 34 plays and performed more than 4,000 performances. In 2019, Louis Mist Theater Company's "Little Red Riding Hood" was performed at the Tianqiao Art Center in Beijing. It was the first time that Pomera's work was performed in mainland China. After four years, "Legend of Fairy Tales" came to the Wuzhen Theater Festival as the closing drama. </p>; <p>;After the performance, some Chinese audiences asked whether they would tour domestically in the future. Wang Jing said that this possibility is slim. The first is due to schedule reasons. The troupe tours hundreds of shows in various countries every year and needs to make reservations at least two years in advance. Secondly, the work requires high stage technology, which is difficult for ordinary theaters to achieve. Thirdly, Pomera has extremely high requirements for stage presentation. </p>; <p>;Wang Jing recalled: "We had a meeting with the technical team in advance as to whether this play could come to Wuzhen at the beginning. The French technical director was very clear that if we couldn't guarantee that they would have no way to come, because they I don’t want the performance to be cut down.”</p>; <p>;The theater cannot hold more than 450 people. Pomera refused to perform in a large theater with thousands of people. “The director is particularly concerned about the audience and needs the audience in the first row and the last row to be You can see clearly." Wang Jing explained to Southern Weekend reporters, "Many of our theaters in China are still based on profitability. If there are less than 1,000 or 2,000 people, they cannot make back their money."</p>; <p>;< /p>;<br>;<hr>;<div>;Get more RSS:<br>;<a href="https://feedx.net" style="color:orange" target="_blank">;https:// feedx.net</a>; <br>;<a href="https://feedx.best" style="color:orange" target="_blank">;https://feedx.best</a>;<br>; </div>; Wed, 15 Nov 2023 21:25:03 +0800 
醉驾女子反诬交警“猥亵”：如此虚假指控，“灵感”从何而来？丨快评http://www.infzm.com/contents/260647 <div>;<i>;2023-11-15 20:00:00</i>;</div>;<p>;Recently, in Huangshi, Hubei, a drunk woman rear-ended the car in front of the traffic police, and the police prepared to drink her. During the test, the woman actually said she wanted to report it to the traffic police for "obscenity." Finally, the police forcefully took the woman to the hospital to collect a blood sample. The test results showed that the alcohol content in her blood was 207.75mg/100ml, which met the standard for drunk driving. The case is currently under further processing. </p>; <p>;From the video of the scene, the woman involved rear-ended her car. The traffic police on duty saw that the woman's face was "red" and asked her to get out of the car and take an alcohol test. The woman involved responded, "I don't blush when I drink." The traffic police required the woman to take a breath test as part of their normal law enforcement, but the response she received was "I'm going to sue you for obscenity." When the traffic police said, "As a citizen (you need to cooperate with law enforcement)," the woman involved simply said, "I'm not a citizen, so I won't brag." Then she had to rely on enforcement to complete the blood sample test. </p>; <p>;The facts of this case are not complicated, and the basic facts are as clear as water. But there are still many points worthy of in-depth discussion. </p>; <p>;First, judging from the facts of this case, in addition to being suspected of dangerous driving, the woman involved is also suspected of other illegal and criminal acts. </p>; <p>;The alcohol content in the blood of the woman involved has exceeded the standard of 80mg/100ml, which is considered drunk driving. Her behavior violated both the "Road Traffic Safety Law of the People's Republic of China" and the "Criminal Law of the People's Republic of China". According to Article 91 of the Road Traffic Safety Law, anyone who drives a motor vehicle drunk will be restrained by the traffic management department of the public security organ until he sobers up, his motor vehicle driving license will be revoked, and he will be investigated for criminal responsibility in accordance with the law; he will not be able to obtain a new motor vehicle driving license within five years; and according to the Criminal Law Article 133: Anyone who drives a motor vehicle drunk on the road shall be sentenced to criminal detention and shall also be fined. </p>; <p>;If the woman involved was only driving drunk and rear-ended the car, her punishment may be limited to the revocation of her driver's license, detention and fines, and she would also be compensated for the loss of the owner of the car in front of her. The problem is that other behaviors of the woman involved at the scene are also suspected of illegal crimes. Her sentence "I will sue you for obscenity" is a public accusation against an individual in a public place, so she must be held accountable for the truth of the accusation. </p>; <p>;The video clearly shows that the traffic police on duty were enforcing the law normally. They reasonably suspected that the owner of the rear-ended car was suspected of drunk driving and required him to undergo an alcohol test. They were completely performing their official duties. According to the "Operational Procedures for Investigating and Dealing with Drunk Driving" attached to the "Traffic Police Road Duty Law Enforcement Work Standards", the traffic police on duty have the right to "require motor vehicle drivers suspected of drunk driving to get out of the vehicle and undergo an alcohol test." Therefore, the public accusations made by the woman involved are outright false accusations, and she should bear corresponding legal responsibility. At a small scale, this is slander and slander, at a larger scale, it is even false accusation and frame-up, because the woman involved also said, "I want to sue you." </p>; <p>;Article 42 of the "Public Security Administration Punishment Law of the People's Republic of China" stipulates that "those who openly insult others or fabricate facts to slander others" "fabricate facts and frame others in an attempt to subject others to criminal prosecution or public security "Management of punishment" is an illegal act and shall be punished with detention and a fine. Article 243 of the Criminal Law also stipulates that fabricating facts to frame others with the intention of subjecting others to criminal prosecution constitutes the crime of false accusation and frame-up. If the circumstances are serious, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not more than three years, criminal detention or surveillance; if serious consequences are caused, the offender shall be sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment of not less than three years and not more than ten years. </p>; <p>;Secondly, the social phenomenon behind this case is even more worrying, that is, some people use their specific identities and speech skills to bypass clear rules and seek privileges for themselves. </p>; <p>;The woman in question reflexively "sue you for obscenity", which shows that similar thinking has been deeply rooted in her bones, that is, she uses false accusations to carry out threats and circumvents clear rules to seek the privilege of impunity for herself. The "inspiration" brought by "false accusations of sexual assault", "false accusations of rape" and "Internet essays" in reality may have long been internalized into the thinking of the parties concerned. The stereotype behind this kind of thinking is enough to make people feel chilling: as long as the matter is settled first If you "make a big fuss" and accuse the other party, you can extort money if you go forward, and you can get away with it if you back off. And even if the words fail, there will be no punishment. </p>; <p>;What is even more worrying is that if there is no video evidence in this case, can the woman involved insist that the traffic police molested her and then counter-sue the traffic police on duty? Can the woman in question use this to blackmail the traffic police on duty and gain the advantage of getting out of jail for herself? It seems that as long as I make such a fuss, others and even public power will "give way to me". This is a trample on justice. </p>; <p>;Thirdly, what is even more serious is that the woman involved made false accusations against state public officials, which is a blatant challenge to the law enforcement authority of the police. According to Article 8 of the "Regulations on Safeguarding the Authority of Civil Police Law Enforcement by Public Security Organs", in the process of performing their duties and exercising their powers in accordance with the law, or because of the performance of their duties and powers in accordance with the law, police officers encounter "threats, intimidation, insults, slander, or threats to themselves and their close relatives, In cases of "harassment", the public security organs should actively safeguard the law enforcement authority of the police. </p>; <p>;Therefore, if the woman involved is not dealt with seriously and her other illegal and criminal acts other than dangerous driving are investigated, it will inevitably bring negative incentives to similar behaviors and stimulate more lawless people to follow the same pattern, and even Continuing to carry out false accusations and creating obstacles for the normal law enforcement of the police is definitely not a blessing to the public interest. This case is still under investigation and the police on duty should be treated fairly to deter those who try to follow suit. </p>; <p>;</p>; Wed, 15 Nov 2023 20:25:03 +0800 
浙江慈溪首富惹麻烦：原高管未能兑现股权激励，举报上市公司危废风险http://www.infzm.com/contents/260676 <div>;<i>;2023-11-15 19:00:00</i>;</div>;<p>;<img alt="August 30, 2023, Shanghai International Power Components and Renewable Energy Management Exhibition Held at the New International Exhibition Center in Pudong, Hesheng Silicon has a booth. Visual China/Photo" src="http://images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/11/15/46bff09a8d.jpg" border= "0" width="1080" height="720" data-src="//images.infzm.com/cms/medias/image/23/11/15/46bff09a8d.jpg" data-key="258419">; </p>; <p style="color: #999999; text-align: center;">;On August 30, 2023, the Shanghai International Power Components and Renewable Energy Management Exhibition was held at the Pudong New International Exhibition Center, Hesheng Silicon Industry Equipped with exhibition stand. Visual China/Picture</p>; <p>;A report letter made the silicon giant with a market value of over 60 billion become a hot topic of public opinion. </p>; <p>;<span>;</span>;<span>;</span>;<span>;2023</span>; On November 12, 2023, the wife of Fang Hongcheng, the former general manager of Hesheng Silicon Industry (603260.SH), verified her identity through the Internet Report: Luo Liguo, chairman of Hoshine Silicon Industry, <span>;coerced the Jiaxing City Government of Zhejiang Province to intervene in the judiciary</span>; and imprisoned Fang Hongchengguo on the grounds of relocating a listed company. <span>;</span>;</p>; <p>;Fang Hongcheng joined Hesheng Silicon Industry in 2009 and served as the general manager of the company since April 2011. He resigned in December 2018. </p>; <p>;<span>;His wife said that after Fang Hongcheng</span>;<span>;resigned</span>;, Luo Liguo refused to fulfill the equity agreement <span>; between the two parties and put pressure on the Jiaxing municipal government, which led to Fang Hongcheng's resignation. He and his brother Fang Hongxing were arrested and detained for 17 months. </p>; <p>;Early the next morning, Hoshine Silicon issued a clarification announcement, disclosing that Fang Hongcheng’s case of bribery and job embezzlement by non-state staff would be heard at the Pinghu People’s Court on the same day. </p>; <p>;The company’s official website shows that Hesheng Silicon Industry was invested and established by Ningbo Hesheng Group in 2005 and listed on the main board of the Shanghai Stock Exchange in 2017. It is the most complete silicon-based full industry chain company in the world and the only one in the industry that also has industrial silicon. It is a high-tech enterprise with production capacity of , organic silicon, polycrystalline silicon, photovoltaic modules, etc. It has production bases in Zhejiang, Xinjiang, Yunnan, Sichuan, Heilongjiang and other places. </p>; <p>;Hopson Silicon Industry’s third quarter report for 2023 shows that the Luo Liguo family is the actual controller of Hopeson Silicon Industry. Luo Liguo and his children collectively hold approximately 78.59% of the equity of the listed company. According to the 2023 Hurun Rich List, the Luo Liguo family ranks 66th with a wealth of 60 billion yuan. </p>; <p>;The person who spoke out on behalf of Fang Hongcheng was his cousin Tong Jianpeng. He told Southern Weekend reporters that Fang Hongcheng’s case did not open as scheduled on November 13, but instead held a full-day pre-trial conference. November 14 is still a pre-trial conference, and the court date is still uncertain. </p>; <p>;On the morning of November 14th and 15th, Fang Hongcheng’s family filed applications for off-site jurisdiction with the Jiaxing Intermediate People’s Court and the Zhejiang Provincial Higher People’s Court respectively, hoping to transfer the case to a people’s court outside Jiaxing for trial. </p>; <p>;What happened behind this real-name reporting controversy? </p>; <h4>;The equity lawsuit interrupted by the criminal case</h4>; <p>;<span>;</span>;<span>;The conflict between Fang Hongcheng and Luo Liguo stems from two equity disputes in recent years. Fang Hongcheng received partial support in the first instance of the case. Southern Weekend reporters obtained relevant referee documents. </span>;</p>; <p>;In September 2015, Fang Hongcheng signed an "Equity Incentive Agreement" with Hesheng Silicon and its employee stockholding platform Ningbo Yingrong Enterprise Management Consulting Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as Ningbo Yingrong), stipulating that Fang Hongcheng It acquired 5% of Ningbo Yingrong's equity at a price of 2.786 million yuan, thus indirectly holding 300,000 shares of Hesheng Silicon Industry. </p>; <p>;<span>;At the same time, the "Equity Incentive Agreement" also stipulates that Fang Hongcheng needs to continue to serve Hesheng Silicon Industry for 5 years after receiving the equity incentive, and not engage in horizontal competition during this period</span>;<span>;, </span>;Do not damage the interests of the company, otherwise you will be held responsible for relevant legal liabilities. </p>; <p>;On October 30, 2017, after the company was listed at an issue price of 19.52 yuan/share, it rose all the way to 252.79 yuan/share, and the company’s market value exceeded 260 billion yuan. </p>; <p>;In 2018, Hoshine Silicon Industry’s annual equity distribution decision was to convert 0.4 shares into shares per share. Fang Hongcheng’s shareholding in Hoshine Silicone Industry therefore increased to 420,000 shares. </p>; <p>;In December of that year, Fang Hongcheng resigned from Hesheng Silicon Industry. Fang Hongcheng said in a self-report that he started his own business after leaving his job. In 2019, he established Zhejiang Xianglin New Materials Co., Ltd. and Zhejiang Yingke New Materials Co., Ltd., which are controlled by him and have no competitive relationship with Hesheng Silicon Industry. </p>; <p>;On April 30, 2021, Fang Hongcheng sued Ningbo Yingrong, with Hesheng Silicon as the third party. Fang said that the lock-up period for its shareholding has expired, and requested that the proceeds from the realization of incentive equity be paid in accordance with the agreement, and the unpaid annual dividends from 2018 to 2020 should be made up. </p>; <p>;The People's Court of Pinghu City, Zhejiang Province found in the first instance that the above-mentioned three parties also signed a "Supplementary Agreement" in 2018, clarifying that Fang Hongcheng agreed to reduce its shareholding by 25% to pay taxes and other fees. . Including the dividend shares distributed in 2018, Fang Hongcheng holds a total of 315,000 shares of Halcyon Silicon. </p>; <p>;In addition, the Pinghu Court held that the non-competition clause was not a condition for obtaining incentive equity, but an obligation after obtaining the equity. The plaintiff Fang Hongcheng should bear legal liability for failing to fulfill the corresponding obligations, rather than losing the incentive equity. </p>; <p>;<span>;On March 28, 2022</span>;, the Pinghu Court supported part of Fang Hongcheng’s petition in the first instance and ruled that Ningbo Yingrong had sold the 315,000 Hesheng Silicon A shares it held. After deducting transaction costs, it was returned to Fang Hongcheng, and the latter was paid stock dividends of 147,600 yuan. Ningbo Yingrong subsequently appealed. </p>; <p>;However, during the second instance of the Jiaxing Intermediate People’s Court, Fang Hongcheng was subject to criminal compulsory measures on suspicion of official embezzlement. </p>; <p>;The Jiaxing Intermediate People’s Court believes that Fang Hongcheng’s prosecution should be dismissed and the relevant materials should be transferred to the public security organs. If the public security organs determine that the case is indeed a civil dispute after review, Fang Hongcheng can assert separate rights. </p>; <p>;On November 29, 2022, the Jiaxing Intermediate People’s Court ruled to revoke the first-instance judgment of the Pinghu Court and reject Fang Hongcheng’s prosecution. </p>; <h4>;Illegal agency holding</h4