 for each converted share distributed by Hesheng Silicon Industry in 2018. </p>; <p>;<span>;On April 25, 2021</span>;, Fang Hongcheng applied to the Hangzhou Arbitration Commission for arbitration over this equity transfer dispute, requiring Luo Liguo to sell 1.4 million shares, <span>; and transfer the proceeds and related shares </span>;The dividends for 2018 and 2019 will be paid to myself. </p>; <p>;<span>;Supervision has always been strict on the issue of equity holdings of listed companies</span>;. The Hangzhou Arbitration Commission cited the Securities Law and the "Administrative Measures for Information Disclosure of Listed Companies" and determined that the agreement between Fang Hongcheng and Luo Liguo on holding shares on behalf of others was invalid, but other clauses were still valid. </p>; <p>;The Hangzhou Arbitration Commission believed that the two parties agreed that Fang Hongcheng would serve Luo Liguo Real Control Company full-time and diligently for at least 5 years starting from January 1, 2017. However, Fang Hongcheng resigned on December 7, 2018 and only performed 40 % of the service period commitment, so you can receive 340,676 shares of Halcyon Silicon and part of the dividends from 2018 to 2020. </p>; <p>;On February 23, 2022, the Hangzhou Arbitration Commission ruled that Luo Liguo reduced and liquidated 340,676 shares of Hesheng Silicon Industry, deducting transaction costs, and paid it to Fang Hongcheng together with a dividend of 376,700 yuan. Luo Liguo also appealed. </p>; <p>;Luo Liguo claimed in the appeal that Fang Hongcheng violated the non-competition agreement by joining Xinyaqiang (603155.SH), a company in the same industry, as deputy general manager and holding 2.81 million shares the same month he resigned from Halcyon Silicon. </p>; <p>;Fang Hongcheng did try to do this. </p>; <p>;Xin Yaqiang’s prospectus shows that the company signed a labor contract with Fang Hongcheng on December 20, 2018, agreeing to appoint Fang Hongche