 40°C is called low boilers, most of which are tetramethylsilane and dimethylsilane. Chlorosilane, trichlorosilane, methyl chloride, etc. The boiling points of low-boiling components are very close, so it is difficult to separate and utilize them. These compounds are flammable and explosive. Among them, tetramethylsilane is included in the national "List of Hazardous Chemicals". </p>; <p>;Hopson Silicon Industry’s prospectus and 2023 semi-annual report both disclosed that low-boiling by-products are the company’s main solid waste and are strictly implemented for external sale. </p>; <p>;According to Fang Hongcheng’s self-report and the materials provided by his family members, in 2011, Hesheng Silicon was in trouble both internally and externally, and was in urgent need of technological transformation and cost reduction. Since the technical transformation of hazardous chemicals production involves government approval, Luo Liguo decided to proceed quickly with all new construction and reconstruction projects, competing with policies to race against time. </p>; <p>;Fang Hongcheng listed 8 illegal new construction and reconstruction projects at that time, all of which failed to go through relevant approval procedures such as safety assessment and environmental assessment as required. The direct economic benefits of most projects were 10 million yuan/year. above. One of the projects is to relatively safely dispose of low-boiling substances classified as hazardous waste in a closed system and turn them into relatively stable "hydrolysis oil". </p>; <p>;The above materials stated that "hydrolysis oil" is the name of Hesheng Silicon Industry. It is a less corrosive, complex, flammable and explosive oily dangerous chemical converted into a low-boiling substance and water through the reaction. Taste. Hesheng Silicon still needs to dispose of the "hydrolysis oil" in a timely manner, otherwise it will cause the company to stop production. </p>; <p>;This job fell to Fang Hongcheng's younger brother Fang Hongxing. "Fang Hongxing risked violations of laws and regulations, safety and environmental risks, and cooperated with others to dispose and utilize 'hydrolysis oil' and obtain profits."</p>; <p >;In April 2019, Fang Hongcheng established Zhejiang Xianglin New Materials Co., Ltd., an asset-light company that produces special silicone coatings. </p>; <p>;<span>;The above materials show that the following month, Hesheng Silicon accused Fang Hongcheng of "breach of trust and damage" on the grounds that Luo Liguo was unaware of the matter and Fang Hongcheng built it without authorization. "interests of listed companies" and reported the case to the Jiaxing Port District Public Security Bureau. </span>;</p>; <p>;After Fang Hongcheng filed lawsuits and arbitrations regarding two equity disputes, in August 2021, Hesheng Silicon reported the case to the Hong Kong Public Security Bureau for the second time on suspicion of Fang Hongcheng being a non-state employee taking bribes. </p>; <p>;The report letter from Fang Hongcheng’s family attached a decision to cancel the case made by the Hong Kong Public Security Bureau on December 31, 2021, stating that there were no criminal facts in Fang Hongcheng’s suspected bribery case by non-state staff and the case was cancelled. </p>; <p>;In fact, Fang Hongcheng and Luo Liguo have argued several times over the disposal of "hydrolysis oil" in the equity dispute litigation. </p>; <p>;Luo Liguo used a set of sales contracts and evaluation reports as evidence, accusing Fang Hongcheng of "selling cheaply" "hydrolysis oil" with an estimated price of more than 10,000 yuan per ton during his tenure, at a price of less than 2,000 yuan/ton. Seeking huge benefits for its affiliated companies. </p>; <p>;<span>;Fang Hongcheng used email exchanges and statements as evidence that his production and sales of "hydrolysis oil" were only in compliance with the decisions of Luo Liguo and other company executives, and were not an act of personal gain. Moreover, the production and sales activities of "hydrolysis oil" are illegal and non-compliant, and will not bring any legitimate benefits to Hesheng Silicon Industry. </span>;</p>; <p>;However, the court focused on the equity dispute between the two and did not make a ruling on the "hydrolysis oil" issue. </p>; <h4>;The company will no longer relocate</h4>; <p>;In June 2022, Fang Hongcheng was placed on file by the Hong Kong Public Security Bureau. In his self-report, he stated that the Fang Hongcheng brothers were summoned on June 13 and placed under "residential surveillance" in a designated residence the next day. </p>; <p>;<span>;Fang Hongcheng and his family believe that the change of events was due to Luo Liguo blackmailing the Jiaxing Municipal Government on the pretext of moving the listed company from Jiaxing City to Cixi, a county-level city under the jurisdiction of Ningbo City. To. According to relevant articles from relevant departments of the Jiaxing Municipal Party Committee in 2018, Hesheng Silicon Industry is the first listed company cultivated by Jiaxing Port Zone. </span>;</p>; <p>;Hopson Silicon stated in the clarification announcement that the company’s registered address is in Jiaxing, but the Jiaxing production base is mainly chemical production facilities and the office conditions are limited, so it will announce the office address in January 2022 Changed to Cixi, Ningbo. </p>; <p>;According to "Ningbo Evening News", Luo Liguo was born in Changhe Town, Cixi, the "hometown of straw hats". He started his business by opening a straw hat factory and is known as the richest man in Cixi. </p>; <p>;According to the clarification announcement, in order to unify the office address and registered address, the company held the 12th meeting of the third board of directors and planned to change the company's address to Cixi. Later, in order to maintain relevant qualification registration, the company terminated the change of compa